    <footer class="footer mt-auto py-3">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="text-muted">
                <ul>
                    <li>Source: <a href="https://coronavirus.data.gov.uk/">https://coronavirus.data.gov.uk/</a></li>
                    <li>Growth = total cases of last 14 days / total cases of 14 days prior to that period</li>
                    <li>Rates per 100,000 resident population</li>
                    <li>Scotland data is updated since 29th July,2020 only.</li>                
                    <li>Middle Super Output Area (MSOA) are small areas with around 7,200 average population. </li>
                    <li>datasets are filtered out where cases are less than 3 to prevent disclosure and protect privacy. Small area data risk disclosure when the numbers are too small.</li>
                </ul>
            </span>
        </div>
    </footer>
